<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 8:57AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT NORTHERN
SMYTH...TAZEWELL...BLAND AND WYTHE COUNTIES THROUGH 930 AM EDT...
At 856 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Kimberling to Burkes Garden to Amonate.
Movement was south at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Bland...
Marion...
Richlands...
Tazewell...
Rural Retreat...
and Cedar Bluff.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
